  <!-- Introducción de la lección (narrative) -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="narrative-leccion-titulo"/></title>
    <p>[+++++++++++++++]</p>
    <p>In grade 2, students estimated, measured, and compared lengths using standard units. They learned how the length of the unit affects measurements.</p>
<p>This lesson introduces the concept of area as students compare the size of different shapes. Students consider what it means for two-dimensional shapes to be larger or cover more space. They measure and describe relative area with increasing precision as they participate in the activities in this lesson.</p>
<p>Give students access to pattern blocks and scissors during the cool-down.</p>
  </paragraphs>
  
  <!-- Preguntas de reflexión profesor -->
